        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "5/2/10 – Set 13-3/8\" 48# H-40 ST&C casing at 805'. Cemented with 450 sx Class \"C\" + 0.125#/sx D130 + 3.76#/sx D20 + 94#/sx D903 + 1.88#/sx S1 + 0.188#/sx D46 (yld 1.97, wt 12.9). Tailed in with 200 sx Class \"C\" + 0.125#/sx D130 + 94#/sx D903 + 0.94#/sx S1 (yld 1.34, wt 14.8). Cement circulated to surface. Tested casing to 600 psi for 30 min, ending 540 psi. NOTE: NMOCD was notified via voicemail and no representative on location to witness cement job. WOC 20 hrs. Reduced hole to 12-1/4\" and resumed drilling.\n\n5/3/10 – TD 12-1/4\" hole at 2:00 AM to 2286'. Set 9-5/8\" 36# J-55 LT&C casing at 2286'. Notified Mike Bratcher-NMOCD of pending cement job but did not witness. Cemented with 550 sx 35:65:6 Poz \"C\" + 0.621#/sx D112 + 27.65#/sx D132 + 5.325#/sx D20 + 4.827#/sx D44 + 61.1#/sx D903 + 0.177#/sx D46 (yld 2.07, wt 12.6). Tailed in with 200 sx Class \"C\" + 94#/sx D903 + 0.1% D13 (yld 1.33, wt 14.8). Cement circulated to surface. Tested casing to 1200 psi for 30 min – no pressure loss. WOC 48 hrs. Reduced hole to 8-3/4\" and resumed drilling.",
